CatDescriptText: Mrs. Rosalle Holmes, charwoman, of McKees Rocks, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "How do you think Soviet Premier Khrushchev's visit to the United States affected relations between our country and Russia? Were you or were you not impressed by his visit to Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "I think that before he came here, Khrushchev didn't think too much of the United States, but since he has seen a lot of our people, and especially, the Pittsburgh people, I think that he will act a little differently."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Rosalle Holmes, wearing eyeglasses and striped dress, standing on Liberty Avenue, in front of Jenkins Arcade with May Building in background, Downtown
